.TH HSH 1 13-01-2022 HSH\ 1 Simple\ Shell\ Manual

.SH NAME
hsh - Simple Shell. Command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
Run ./hsh [command] [argument] and echo "[command] [argument]" | ./hsh for non-interactive mode.

.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple Shell functionality of "sh".

.SH COMPILATION
gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh

.SH MODES
The shell can is how the shell is normally used, commands. In the non-interactive the command to the executable file with a pipe operator. In the "EXAMPLES" use them.

.SH EXAMPLES
- Interactive mode:
.TP
\r$ ./hsh
.TP
\r\rhsh$ ls -l
.TP
- Non-interactive mode:
.TP
\recho "ls -l" | ./hsh

.SH AUTHORS
